"title": "5882: impartiality",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5882",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The ability to be unbiased towards any one race, class or person. This attitude is demonstrated by God and is to be emulated by the human race.</p>\n<h2>God is impartial</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17\">DEU 10:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:7\">2CH 19:7</a></p>\n<h3>God treats people impartially</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:45\">MAT 5:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:3\">JOB 25:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:19\">JOB 34:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:2\">PRO 22:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:11\">ROM 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:9\">EPH 6:9</a></p>\n<h3>God judges impartially</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:25\">COL 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:11-Job34:12\">JOB 34:11–34:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:12\">PSA 62:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:10\">JER 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:9-Rom2:11\">ROM 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:17\">1PE 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:12\">REV 22:12</a></p>\n<h3>God does not distinguish between people on the basis of external appearance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:10-Ps147:11\">PSA 147:10–147:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:25\">JER 9:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:15\">LUK 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:6\">GAL 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:23\">REV 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>God does not discriminate against different races or classes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:34-Acts10:35\">ACT 10:34–10:35</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:28\">GAL 3:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:18\">DEU 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:19\">JOB 34:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:28\">ACT 10:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:7-Acts15:9\">ACT 15:7–15:9</a></p>\n<h2>The impartiality of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's teaching was impartial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:21\">LUK 20:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:16\">MAT 22:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:14\">MRK 12:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1-Matt20:16\">MAT 20:1–20:16</a> <em>a parable of Jesus Christ about divine impartiality</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ showed impartiality in his dealings with people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:9\">JHN 4:9</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ contravened accepted boundaries of partiality in this encounter.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10-Matt9:12\">MAT 9:10–9:12</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:15-Mark2:17\">MRK 2:15–2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29-Luke5:31\">LUK 5:29–5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:22–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:26-Mark7:29\">MRK 7:26–7:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:20-Matt20:23\">MAT 20:20–20:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:35-Mark10:40\">MRK 10:35–10:40</a></p>\n<h2>Impartiality commended</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:1\">JAS 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:21\">PRO 28:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:3-1Cor3:4\">1CO 3:3–3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:6-1Cor4:7\">1CO 4:6–4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:21\">1TI 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:9\">JAS 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Humanity should judge impartially</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:23-Prov24:25\">PRO 24:23–24:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:16\">EXO 18:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:17\">DEU 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:19\">DEU 16:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:17\">DEU 24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:15\">PRO 17:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:5\">PRO 18:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:9\">MAL 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Showing impartiality to all people is commanded</h2>\n<h3>Impartiality to foreigners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21\">EXO 22:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:9\">EXO 23:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:33-Lev19:34\">LEV 19:33–19:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:15-Num15:16\">NUM 15:15–15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:12\">ROM 10:12</a></p>\n<h3>Impartiality to children</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:15-Deut21:17\">DEU 21:15–21:17</a></p>\n<h3>Impartiality to the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:6\">EXO 23:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:3\">EXO 23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:15\">LEV 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:7\">PRO 29:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:2-Jas2:7\">JAS 2:2–2:7</a></p>\n<h2>Ways to avoid partiality</h2>\n<h3>By not accepting bribes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:8\">EXO 23:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:18\">JOB 36:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:27\">PRO 15:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:23\">ISA 1:23</a></p>\n<h3>By not following the crowd</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:2\">EXO 23:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:15\">MRK 15:15</a></p>\n<h2>Christians should be partial towards spiritual principles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24\">MAT 6:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:13\">LUK 16:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:30\">MAT 12:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:23\">LUK 11:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:13-Matt7:14\">MAT 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:39-Mark9:40\">MRK 9:39–9:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:49-Luke9:50\">LUK 9:49–9:50</a></p>\n<h2>Examples where impartiality is absent</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:27-Gen25:28\">GEN 25:27–25:28</a> <em>Isaac and Rebekah to Jacob and Esau</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:30-Gen29:32\">GEN 29:30–29:32</a> <em>Jacob to Leah and Rachel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:3-Gen37:4\">GEN 37:3–37:4</a> <em>Jacob to Joseph and his brothers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:4-1Sam1:6\">1SA 1:4–1:6</a> <em>Elkanah to Hannah and Peninnah</em></p>",
